<https://guia-kg.skai.etsisi.upm.es/resource/93000963/2025-26/evaluation> a ns1:EvaluationSystem ;
    ns1:evaluationDescription """According to the Normativa de Evaluación del Aprendizaje de la Universidad Politécnica de Madrid, evaluation will assess if students have acquired all the competences of the subject. Thus, evaluation through global assessment will be carried out considering all the evaluation techniques used in continuous evaluation (EX, ET, TG, etc.), and will be celebrated in the exam period approved by Junta de Escuela for the current academic semester and year. Evaluation activities that assess learning outcomes that cannot be evaluated through a single exam can be carried out along the semester.
- In order to pass the course, students must obtain a minimum grade of 5/10
- All assignments must reflect the personal work and teamwork of the student, Detected copies will automatically mean failing the course.

Progressive evaluation:
- Midterm Report - 25%
- Final Written Report and Presentation - 40%
- Team Evaluations 15% - (Individual- 10% mentor - 5% team members evaluate each other)
- Individual Performance, presentations, questions, quizzes and Progress Deliverables - Individual- 20%

Global evaluation:
- Midterm Report - 25%
- Final Written Report and Presentation - 40%

Extraordinary evaluation:
- Final report and presentation: 100%"""@es ;
